{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"82c5269e-1908-48f0-8fe4-dd834ae64eee","content":"The Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalent:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- \\\n  --treenode-filter \"/*[Tag=Integration]\" \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\nKey changes:\n| VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|--------|---------------------------|\n| `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` | `--treenode-filter \"/*[Tag=Integration]\"` |\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang --blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\nRequired NuGet packages in your test project:\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump\" />\n```\n\nNote: everything after `--` is forwarded to the testing platform. If your test framework supports the VSTest `--filter` syntax via a compatibility shim, you can keep using `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` after `--` instead of the tree-node filter.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"45693821-5e67-4825-b79d-cb6b71ff50d4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nKey differences with Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n- `--filter` becomes `--filter`  (same, or `--treenode-filter`)\n- `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` becomes `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura`\n- `--blame-crash` becomes `--crashdump`\n- `--blame-hang` becomes `--hangdump`\n\n\n- `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` becomes `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\nThe Microsoft.Testing.Platform has a different command-line interface than VSTest, though `dotnet test` still works as the entry point—you'll need the TrxReport extension for TRX output and the arguments map differently for filtering, coverage collection, and diagnostic dumps.\n\nWhen passing platform-specific options through `dotnet test`, they go after `--`, so you'd structure it like running the test with filter criteria, then specifying report format, coverage, and dump options all in one command.\n\nActually, I need to reconsider how argument forwarding works with the newer integration—`dotnet test` might handle this differently than I initially thought. the filter syntax differs between the old VSTest approach and the new Microsoft.Testing.Platform—I can use `--filter` for compatibility or `--treenode-filter` for the platform-specific syntax, and I need to verify which NuGet packages are required for .NET 8 to enable this properly. I'm realizing the compatibility layer likely still accepts the traditional `--filter` syntax, so I can show both approaches—the familiar VSTest-style filter and the native tree-node filter syntax that Microsoft.Testing.Platform uses—along with the required extension packages.","outputTokens":1638,"requestId":"BC30:926CA:1B140C5:1E28AEE:69FA9054"},"id":"46e31d98-b132-4967-8658-67c69ba7bc8a","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:50:53.287Z","parentId":"67ec5346-0d98-4378-9e73-0adb6a3801fc"}
